<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1464,2030]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1608,1634]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body surface sparsely papillate. Dorsal tentacular cirri 1.5x longer than ventral ones. All dorsal cirri similar in length. Parapodial glands from first chaetiger on dorsal surface and from the sixth chaetiger on ventral surface. Neurochaetae smooth capillaries, limbate with limbus smooth, unidentate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1464,2030]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1716,1742]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Description.</emphasis>
Fixed specimen whitish with dark parapodial glands on dorsal and ventral surfaces (
<figureCitation box="[1308,1375,1716,1742]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A–C; 8A, B). The following description is based on the 
<typeStatus box="[710,812,1752,1778]" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">holotype</typeStatus>
: size 
<quantity box="[873,987,1752,1778]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.089" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="20.89">20.89 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1057,1157,1752,1778]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="66" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.90 mm</quantity>
wide at widest point (including parapodia), 92 chaetigers. Body dorsoventrally flattened (
<figureCitation box="[890,980,1788,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[991,1029,1788,1814]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1145,1169]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,241,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-46@12.[151,1436,236,1121]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body, dorsal view. B. Parapodium from chaetiger 15, posterior view. C. Chaetae from midbody, dorsal view. D. Anterior body, dorsal view. Scale bars: 500 µm (A), 150 µm (B), 50 µm (C), 200 µm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574047/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">8A</figureCitation>
). Body surface with papillae minute and sparse, papillae abundant on cirrophores of tentacular and dorsal cirri, antennae and parapodial cirri (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1423,1824,1850]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1145,1169]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,241,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-46@12.[151,1436,236,1121]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body, dorsal view. B. Parapodium from chaetiger 15, posterior view. C. Chaetae from midbody, dorsal view. D. Anterior body, dorsal view. Scale bars: 500 µm (A), 150 µm (B), 50 µm (C), 200 µm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574047/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). Prostomium with lateral antennae inserted on posterior margin; median antenna and eyes absent (
<figureCitation box="[1233,1319,1860,1886]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1330,1368,1860,1886]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1145,1169]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,241,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-46@12.[151,1436,236,1121]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body, dorsal view. B. Parapodium from chaetiger 15, posterior view. C. Chaetae from midbody, dorsal view. D. Anterior body, dorsal view. Scale bars: 500 µm (A), 150 µm (B), 50 µm (C), 200 µm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574047/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">8D</figureCitation>
). Two biarticulated palps conical (
<figureCitation box="[458,545,1896,1922]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[556,593,1896,1922]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1145,1169]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,241,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-46@12.[151,1436,236,1121]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body, dorsal view. B. Parapodium from chaetiger 15, posterior view. C. Chaetae from midbody, dorsal view. D. Anterior body, dorsal view. Scale bars: 500 µm (A), 150 µm (B), 50 µm (C), 200 µm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574047/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">8D</figureCitation>
), palpophore large and palpostyle diminutive. Proboscis not observed. Peristomium dorsally distinct from prostomium with two pairs of tentacular cirri. Dorsal tentacular cirri 1.5x longer than ventral ones and 2.2x longer than lateral antennae. Parapodia sub-biramous and inflated; all parapodia have ventral and dorsal cirri in conical shape (
<figureCitation box="[521,608,2004,2030]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1145,1169]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,241,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-46@12.[151,1436,236,1121]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body, dorsal view. B. Parapodium from chaetiger 15, posterior view. C. Chaetae from midbody, dorsal view. D. Anterior body, dorsal view. Scale bars: 500 µm (A), 150 µm (B), 50 µm (C), 200 µm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574047/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="66">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal cirri of first chaetiger 1.2x longer than second one, and as long as following cirri (
<figureCitation box="[330,419,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
); ventral cirri shorter than dorsal cirri. Cirrophores of dorsal cirri thick and globose, twice as long as cirrostyles. Parapodial glands darkly pigmented, some brownish to reddish, concentrated in elliptical clusters, present on dorsal surfaces of all parapodia, and on ventral surface from the chaetiger 6 and some absent between chaetigers 30 and 35 (
<figureCitation box="[466,530,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A–C), ventral glands smaller than dorsal ones. Neuropodial lobes conical, smaller than dorsal cirri. Neurochaetae smooth capillaries variable in length, limbate with limbus smooth and unidentate tips; up to seven neurochaetae per fascicle (
<figureCitation box="[641,730,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1145,1169]" captionTargetBox="[155,1429,241,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-46@12.[151,1436,236,1121]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body, dorsal view. B. Parapodium from chaetiger 15, posterior view. C. Chaetae from midbody, dorsal view. D. Anterior body, dorsal view. Scale bars: 500 µm (A), 150 µm (B), 50 µm (C), 200 µm (D)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574047" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574047/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Posterior end abruptly tapering due to posterior regeneration, 12 regenerating segments; parapodial glands barely visible in regenerated segments (
<figureCitation box="[1097,1184,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Pygidium with small papillae present on the posterior margin; anal cirri absent (
<figureCitation box="[805,894,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1329,1353]" captionTargetBox="[172,1430,466,1300]" captionTargetId="figure-151@11.[158,1430,453,1308]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Pilargis falconae sp. nov. A. Whole body. B. Anterior end. C. Posterior body showing regeneration. All images in dorsal view.Abbreviations. Dc: dorsal cirrus, La: lateral antenna, Pgl: parapodial gland, Pp: palp, Pt: prostomium, Py: pygidium, Reg: regeneration, Tdc: tentacular dorsal cirrus, Tvc: tentacular ventral cirrus. Scale bars: 2 mm (A), 200 µm (B, C)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4574045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4574045/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
