<subSubSection box="[199,1185,1471,1498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1471,2037]" box="[199,1185,1471,1498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1471,1497]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Distribution.</emphasis>
Atlantic Ocean—Brazil, Campos Basin, specimen examined in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1471,2037]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1508,1534]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Remarks.</emphasis>
There is no doubt that the specimen examined belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saint-Joseph" authorityYear="1899" box="[1116,1205,1507,1533]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1116,1205,1507,1533]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Pilargis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, due to the absence of notochaetae. Among species with papillae small and sparsely distributed, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[1031,1160,1543,1570]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae">
<emphasis box="[1031,1048,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1064,1160,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris, 2006" authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris" authorityYear="2006" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="angeli">
<emphasis box="[1333,1350,1544,1569]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1366,1436,1543,1569]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">angeli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Salazar-Vallejo, S. I. &amp; Harris, L. H." box="[151,504,1579,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" pagination="119 - 159" refId="ref15131" refString="Salazar-Vallejo, S. I. &amp; Harris, L. H. (2006) Revision of Pilargis de Saint-Joseph, 1899 (Annelida, Polychaeta, Pilargidae). Journal of Natural History, 40, 119 - 159. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930600594212" type="journal article" year="2006">Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Monro, 1933" authorityName="Monro" authorityYear="1933" box="[516,828,1579,1606]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="berkeleyae">
<emphasis box="[516,533,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[548,669,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">berkeleyae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Monro, C. C. A." box="[678,828,1580,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" pagination="673 - 675" refId="ref14164" refString="Monro, C. C. A. (1933) On a new species of polychaete of the genus Pilargis from Friday Harbour, Washington. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 10, 11, 673 - 675. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222933308673741" type="journal article" year="1933">Monro, 1933</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hartman, 1947" authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1947" box="[840,1157,1579,1606]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[840,857,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[873,977,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">maculata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hartman, O." box="[985,1157,1580,1606]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" pagination="483 - 523" refId="ref13641" refString="Hartman, O. (1947) Polychaetous annelids. Part VIII. Pilargidae. Allan Hancock Pacific Expeditions, 10 (5),, 483 - 523." type="journal article" year="1947">Hartman, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Intes &amp; Le Loeuff, 1975" authorityName="Intes &amp; Le Loeuff" authorityYear="1975" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[1218,1235,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1250,1343,1579,1605]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">modesta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Intes, A. &amp; Le Loeuff, P." pageId="11" pageNumber="67" pagination="267 - 321" refId="ref13777" refString="Intes, A. &amp; Le Loeuff, P. (1975) Les annelides polychetes de Cote d'Ivoire. I. Polychetes errantes - compte rendu systematique. Cahiers O. R. S. T. O. M., Serie oceanographie 13 (4), 267 - 321." type="journal article" year="1975">Intes &amp; Le Loeuff, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<tableCitation box="[396,482,1615,1642]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="13.[151,239,512,538]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="TABLE 2. Main morphological features of Pilargis species presently known." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF03666BFFCBFFAEFF22FD8CB9B6FDF7" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" tableUuid="DF03666BFFCBFFAEFF22FD8CB9B6FDF7">Table 2</tableCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salazar-Vallejo &amp; Harris" authorityYear="2006" box="[620,722,1615,1642]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="angeli">
<emphasis box="[620,637,1616,1641]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[652,722,1615,1641]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">angeli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different in lacking parapodial glands either on the dorsal or ventral surface, and in having dorsal tentacular cirri 1.2x longer than ventral ones, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta, 2020" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[1163,1291,1651,1678]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1163,1180,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1195,1291,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1300,1391,1652,1678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1300,1391,1652,1678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has dorsal and ventral parapodial glands, and dorsal tentacular cirri 1.5x longer than ventral ones. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monro" authorityYear="1933" box="[1218,1436,1687,1713]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="berkeleyae">
<emphasis box="[1218,1436,1687,1713]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Pilargis berkeleyae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta, 2020" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[299,430,1723,1750]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[299,316,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[334,430,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[440,533,1724,1750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[440,533,1724,1750]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having parapodial glands only in the most posterior segments and limbate chaetae bidendate, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta, 2020" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[439,567,1759,1786]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[439,456,1760,1785]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[471,567,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[576,667,1760,1786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[576,667,1760,1786]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has parapodial glands from anterior chaetigers and limbate chaetae unidentate. Both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1947" box="[346,482,1795,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[346,363,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[378,482,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Intes &amp; Le Loeuff" authorityYear="1975" box="[540,665,1795,1822]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[540,557,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[572,665,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have dorsal parapodial glands from the first chaetiger. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hartman" authorityYear="1947" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1796,1821]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,255,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta, 2020" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[409,538,1831,1858]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[409,426,1832,1857]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[442,538,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[547,639,1832,1858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[547,639,1832,1858]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having bidentate capillaries, sub-spherical glands on the tentacular segment (peristomium), ventral glands from the first or second chaetigers, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[1076,1205,1867,1894]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae">
<emphasis box="[1076,1093,1868,1893]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1109,1205,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has limbate chaetae unidentate, lacks glands in the peristomium, and has ventral glands from the sixth chaetiger. On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Intes &amp; Le Loeuff" authorityYear="1975" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="modesta">
<emphasis box="[1412,1429,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,244,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">modesta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having spherical-shaped glands located in the cirrophore, and cirrostyles one-fifth the length of cirrophores, while 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta, 2020" authorityName="Ribeiro &amp; Barbosa &amp; Freitas &amp; Zanol &amp; Glasby &amp; Ruta" authorityYear="2020" box="[362,489,1975,2002]" class="Polychaeta" family="Pilargidae" genus="Pilargis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="falconae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[362,379,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[393,489,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">falconae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[496,585,1976,2002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[496,585,1976,2002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has glands in elliptical clusters on the base of parapodia and cirrostyles half the length of cirrophores.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="68" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,150,212]" pageId="12" pageNumber="68">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,150,176]" pageId="12" pageNumber="68">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name is in honour of Ana Paula da Costa Falcão, marine biologist and member of the PETRO- BRAS technical staff who collaborated in the HABITATS Project.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
